## 2. OWASP TOP 10

### A01 — Broken Access Control
Flag: database lookup by user-controlled ID without ownership verification (IDOR)
  Bad:  db.find({ id: req.params.id })
  Good: db.find({ id: req.params.id, ownerId: req.user.id })
Flag: routes that mutate data or return sensitive resources without authorization middleware
Flag: path traversal — fs.readFile(path.join('/uploads', req.params.file)) without basename sanitization
Flag: admin or privileged endpoints accessible without role check
Flag: CORS allowing credentialed cross-origin reads from untrusted origins

### A02 — Cryptographic Failures
Flag: hardcoded passwords, API keys, tokens, or connection strings in source code
Flag: weak password hashing — md5(), sha1(), sha256() without salt — replace with bcrypt/argon2/scrypt
Flag: sensitive data in log statements — passwords, tokens, PII, card numbers
Flag: JWT missing exp claim, accepting alg: none, or secret stored inline in code
Flag: TLS disabled or certificate validation bypassed
Flag: symmetric keys or private keys committed to repository
Flag: HTTP used for endpoints transmitting credentials or personal data

### A03 — Injection
Flag: SQL string concatenation — "SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = " + userId
Flag: shell injection — exec(userInput), os.system(data), child_process.exec(req.body.cmd)
Flag: eval() with user-controlled data — eval(req.body.code), Function(userInput)()
Flag: server-side template injection — user input inserted into Jinja2, Pug, Twig, Handlebars without escaping
Flag: NoSQL injection — db.find({ $where: userInput }), unsanitized MongoDB operators
Flag: XXE — XML parsers with external entity processing enabled on user-supplied XML

### A04 — Insecure Design
Flag: login, registration, or password-reset endpoints without rate limiting middleware
Flag: API endpoints accepting unbounded input without size or type validation
Flag: missing CAPTCHA or anti-automation protection on public-facing forms

### A05 — Security Misconfiguration
Flag: cors({ origin: '*' }) on authenticated or credentialed routes
Flag: error responses returning stack traces — res.json({ error: err.stack })
Flag: debug=True or NODE_ENV=development set outside local-only config
Flag: missing security headers — no helmet, no CSP, no HSTS, no X-Frame-Options
Flag: default credentials not changed (admin/admin, root/root)
Flag: directory listing enabled on web server

### A06 — Vulnerable Components
Flag: dependencies with known CVEs in package.json, requirements.txt, go.mod, pom.xml
Flag: overly broad version ranges for security-sensitive packages — "^1.x", ">=1.0"
Flag: no Dependabot, Renovate, or equivalent automated update configuration
Flag: EOL runtime versions — Node.js 14, Python 3.7, Java 8 without LTS

### A07 — Authentication Failures
Flag: passwords hashed with MD5, SHA1, or unsalted SHA256
Flag: JWT access tokens without exp claim or with expiry > 15 minutes
Flag: missing server-side session invalidation on logout
Flag: login endpoint with no rate limiting, no account lockout, no CAPTCHA
Flag: remember-me or persistent tokens stored in plaintext in database

### A08 — Software and Data Integrity Failures
Flag: CI/CD pipeline with no SAST or SCA step
Flag: GitHub Actions with pull_request_target checking out fork code (code injection risk)
Flag: Actions pinned to mutable tags — uses: actions/checkout@v4 — must use SHA
Flag: permissions: write-all at workflow or job level without justification
Flag: unsigned container images pushed to registry

### A09 — Logging and Monitoring Failures
Flag: sensitive endpoints with no access logging
Flag: failed authentication events not explicitly logged
Flag: log statements including passwords, tokens, card numbers, or PII
Flag: no correlation ID or request ID in log entries across multi-service codebase

### A10 — SSRF
Flag: server-side fetch from user-controlled URL without allowlist validation
  Bad:  fetch(req.body.url)
  Good: if (!ALLOWED_HOSTS.includes(new URL(req.body.url).hostname)) throw new Error('Forbidden')
Flag: redirect following enabled on server-side HTTP clients with untrusted input
Flag: cloud metadata endpoints reachable without IMDS protection — 169.254.169.254, metadata.google.internal

