## 4. GDPR

Flag: personal data in log statements — email, IP, full name, phone, national ID, date of birth
  Bad:  logger.info('User login', { email, ip: req.ip })
  Good: logger.info('User login', { userId: user.id })

Flag: analytics or tracking loaded without consent gate — Google Analytics (gtag.js, analytics.js), Mixpanel, Segment, Hotjar, Facebook Pixel loaded unconditionally at page load
  Violation: GDPR Art. 6 and Art. 7 — requires freely given, specific, informed consent

Flag: no privacy policy link in registration, onboarding, or checkout flows

Flag: user data transmitted to third-party APIs without disclosed lawful basis

Flag: no data deletion mechanism — no endpoint, no admin function, no scheduled purge for user data (Art. 17 right to erasure)

Flag: no DSAR handler — users cannot export their own data (Art. 20 data portability)

Flag: cookies set without SameSite=Strict or Lax, Secure, and HttpOnly attributes

Flag: PII stored in URL query parameters — /search?email=user@example.com (logged by servers and proxies)

Flag: consent not stored with version and timestamp — no evidence of consent version management

