## 5. ISO 27001

### A.8.9 — Configuration Management
Flag: hardcoded secrets, credentials, or API keys in source code or committed config files
Flag: .env files not listed in .gitignore
Flag: infrastructure configuration not managed as code

### A.8.24 — Cryptography
Flag: deprecated algorithms — DES, 3DES, RC4, MD5, SHA1 used for hashing, signing, or encryption
Flag: RSA keys shorter than 2048 bits or EC keys shorter than 256 bits
Flag: cryptographic keys hardcoded instead of managed via KMS or secrets manager

### A.8.25 — Secure Development Lifecycle
Flag: CI/CD pipeline without security gates — no SAST, no DAST, no SCA
Flag: no security-focused code review for sensitive changes (auth, crypto, payment processing)

### A.8.28 — Secure Coding
Flag: unparameterized database queries and missing input validation
Flag: missing output encoding before rendering user-controlled data in HTML

### A.8.12 — Information Leakage Prevention
Flag: no secrets scanning configured in CI/CD — gitleaks, trufflehog
Flag: verbose API errors exposing internal paths, technology versions, or stack traces

### A.5.36 — Compliance
Flag: SECURITY.md absent from repository root
Flag: no vulnerability disclosure contact or process documented

