## 6. PCI-DSS

Apply when code references card processing, payment APIs, or financial transaction handling.

Flag: PAN pattern in source code or logs
  Pattern: Visa \b4[0-9]{12}(?:[0-9]{3})?\b, Mastercard \b5[1-5][0-9]{14}\b

Flag: CVV/CVC/CVV2 stored in any persistent storage — strictly prohibited by PCI-DSS Req. 3.2.1

Flag: payment card data transmitted without TLS

Flag: direct card number handling without an approved tokenization provider or payment gateway

Flag: cardholder data access not logged with user identity, timestamp, and action — Req. 10

Flag: no MFA on administrative access to systems that store, process, or transmit cardholder data

Flag: no WAF or intrusion detection for payment-processing infrastructure

Flag: overly permissive access to payment database tables — no role-based restriction

