## 7. NIST SP 800-53

### IA-5 — Authenticator Management
Flag: passwords stored without strong adaptive hashing — bcrypt, argon2id, or scrypt required
Flag: default credentials not changed in application or infrastructure configuration
Flag: API keys without rotation mechanism or expiry

### AU-2 / AU-12 — Audit Logging
Flag: authentication events (success and failure) not logged
Flag: privileged or administrative actions not logged
Flag: log entries missing timestamp, user identity, event type, or outcome

### SC-8 — Transmission Security
Flag: data transmitted over unencrypted channels
Flag: TLS certificate validation disabled — verify=False, rejectUnauthorized: false, InsecureSkipVerify: true
Flag: sensitive data in GET URL parameters — logged by intermediaries

### SC-28 — Data at Rest Protection
Flag: database fields containing PII or secrets not encrypted
Flag: encryption at rest not enabled on storage volumes or database instances
Flag: encryption keys stored alongside the data they protect

### SA-11 — Developer Security Testing
Flag: no SAST tool configured in development pipeline
Flag: no DAST referenced for pre-production testing
Flag: security findings not tracked in issue tracker

### CM-6 — Configuration Settings
Flag: insecure default configuration deployed without hardening
Flag: infrastructure configuration not aligned with CIS Benchmarks

### SI-10 — Input Validation
Flag: user inputs accepted without type, length, format, or range validation
Flag: file upload endpoints without MIME type validation and size limits
Flag: GraphQL without depth limiting or complexity analysis

