## 9. CIS BENCHMARKS

### Docker

CIS 4.1 — Flag: Dockerfile without USER instruction — container runs as root
  Fix:
    RUN addgroup -S appgroup && adduser -S appuser -G appgroup
    USER appuser

CIS 4.5 — Flag: mutable base image tags — FROM node:latest, FROM python:3, FROM ubuntu
  Fix: FROM node:20-alpine@sha256:<digest>

CIS 4.6 — Flag: no HEALTHCHECK instruction in Dockerfile
  Fix: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1

CIS 4.3 — Flag: missing .dockerignore or .dockerignore not excluding .git, node_modules, .env, *.key, *.pem

CIS 3.x — Flag: ADD used for local files — use COPY instead

CIS 4.x — Flag: ARG or ENV used to bake secrets into image layers

### Kubernetes

Flag: securityContext.privileged: true on any container
Flag: allowPrivilegeEscalation not explicitly set to false
Flag: securityContext.runAsNonRoot absent or false
Flag: readOnlyRootFilesystem absent or false
Flag: missing resources.limits.cpu and resources.limits.memory — enables resource exhaustion attacks
Flag: NetworkPolicy absent from namespace — all pods communicate freely
Flag: secrets base64-encoded in ConfigMap instead of Secret resource
Flag: ClusterRoleBinding to cluster-admin for application service accounts
Flag: wildcard RBAC — verbs: ["*"] or resources: ["*"]
Flag: automountServiceAccountToken: true on pods not requiring API server access

### GitHub Actions / CI-CD

Flag: pull_request_target with actions/checkout of fork branch — enables arbitrary code execution
Flag: untrusted input in run: step — echo "${{ github.event.pull_request.title }}" (injection via PR title)
Flag: Actions pinned to mutable tags — uses: actions/checkout@v4 — must use full SHA
Flag: permissions: write-all at workflow or job level
Flag: secrets hardcoded in workflow YAML — use ${{ secrets.NAME }}
Flag: no SAST step in CI pipeline
Flag: no SCA step in CI pipeline
Flag: no secrets scanning step in CI pipeline — gitleaks, trufflehog

### Terraform / IaC

Flag: security_groups with cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"] on port 22, 3389, 5432, 6379, 27017
Flag: S3 bucket without block_public_acls = true and block_public_policy = true
Flag: RDS without storage_encrypted = true and deletion_protection = true
Flag: IAM policy with "Action": "*" or "Resource": "*"
Flag: CloudTrail not enabled or log file validation disabled
Flag: credentials hardcoded in .tf or .tfvars files
Flag: remote state without encryption or state locking configured

