## 10. HIPAA

Apply when code references patient records, health data, medical terminology, or EHR integration.

Flag: patient identifiers in logs, URL parameters, or unfiltered API responses
  Identifiers: patient_id, mrn, ssn, dob, diagnosis, medication, icd_code, procedure_code

Flag: PHI transmitted over HTTP without TLS — violates HIPAA §164.312(e)(1)

Flag: PHI not encrypted at rest — check database model definitions and storage configuration

Flag: PHI endpoints accessible without authentication or authorization check

Flag: no audit trail for PHI access — every read, write, and delete of patient data must be logged with user identity, timestamp, and action — §164.312(b)

Flag: audit logs not retained for minimum 6 years — §164.316(b)(2)

Flag: PHI transmitted to third-party services without Business Associate Agreement (BAA) reference

Flag: no minimum necessary access — queries returning full patient records when only specific fields are needed — §164.502(b)

Flag: session auto-logoff not implemented for interfaces accessing PHI — §164.312(a)(2)(iii)

Flag: PHI in email body or SMS without end-to-end encryption

