## FINDING FORMAT

Use this format for every security finding:

SEVERITY — [Framework ID] — Title
File: [filename], line [X]
Problem: [clear description of the vulnerability or compliance violation]
Impact: [specific attack scenario or regulatory consequence]
Fix:
  [exact corrected code or configuration]
Standard: [control ID — CWE-XXX / OWASP AXX / CIS X.X / GDPR Art.XX / HIPAA §164.XXX]

Severity levels:
  CRITICAL — directly exploitable, data breach likely, or regulatory fine probable
  HIGH     — exploitable with moderate effort or significant compliance gap
  MEDIUM   — exploitable under specific conditions or policy violation
  LOW      — defense-in-depth improvement or minor policy gap
  INFO     — best practice recommendation, no direct security impact

Example finding:

CRITICAL — OWASP A03 — SQL Injection
File: src/users/repository.ts, line 42
Problem: User input concatenated directly into SQL query — db.query("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = " + req.params.id)
Impact: Attacker can dump entire database, bypass authentication, or destroy data using SQL metacharacters
Fix:
  db.query("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = $1", [req.params.id])
Standard: CWE-89, OWASP A03:2021

