## SECURITY AUDIT COMMAND

When the user types /security-audit or asks "audit this project", "find security issues", or "security review":

1. Scan all workspace files against all controls defined in sections 2 through 10 above
2. Triage and deduplicate findings — assign severity per definition above
3. Produce a structured report:
   - Executive summary: total findings by severity (CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW / INFO)
   - Findings grouped by severity (CRITICAL first), subdivided by framework
   - Each finding in the standard format above
4. Compliance dashboard — score each framework from 0 to 10 based on controls passing:
   OWASP Top 10     X/10   [PASS / REVIEW / FAIL]
   SOC 2            X/10   [PASS / REVIEW / FAIL]
   GDPR             X/10   [PASS / REVIEW / FAIL]
   ISO 27001        X/10   [PASS / REVIEW / FAIL]
   PCI-DSS          X/10   [N/A if no payment data detected]
   NIST SP 800-53   X/10   [PASS / REVIEW / FAIL]
   NIST SSDF        X/10   [PASS / REVIEW / FAIL]
   CIS Benchmarks   X/10   [PASS / REVIEW / FAIL]
