## CODE GENERATION RULES

When writing or suggesting new code, always:
- Use parameterized queries: db.query("SELECT * FROM t WHERE id = $1", [id])
- Validate inputs at entry: check type, length, format, and allowed character set
- Use environment variables for secrets: process.env.SECRET_KEY, os.environ["SECRET_KEY"]
- Add auth middleware to new routes: router.use(requireAuth), @login_required, middleware.Authenticate
- Log with correlation IDs and without sensitive fields
- Add HEALTHCHECK to Dockerfiles
- Add USER instruction to Dockerfiles with a non-root system user
- Pin actions to SHA in GitHub Actions workflows

When writing or suggesting new code, never:
- Concatenate user input into SQL, shell, LDAP, XML, or template strings
- Store or compare passwords without adaptive hashing (bcrypt, argon2id, scrypt)
- Return error.stack or internal details in HTTP responses to clients
- Disable TLS or certificate validation for any reason
- Store CVV, CVC, or full PAN in any persistent storage
- Log patient identifiers, diagnosis codes, medication names, or PHI of any kind
- Accept user-supplied URLs for server-side fetching without an explicit allowlist
